Package: jack
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, systemd
Recommends: dnsmasq (>= 2.80), nftables (>= 0.9), wireguard-tools
Description: Network gateway management tool
 Jack is a comprehensive network gateway management tool that provides
 a unified interface for managing firewall, DHCP, DNS, VPN, and routing
 configurations through a plugin-based architecture.
 .
 Features:
  - Plugin-based architecture with 6 core plugins (nftables, dnsmasq, wireguard,
    monitoring, leds, sqlite3)
  - Firewall management with nftables (zones, forwarding, NAT, port forwarding)
  - DHCP and DNS server configuration via dnsmasq
  - WireGuard VPN server and client support
  - LED control for hardware indicators
  - SQLite3 logging and data storage
  - Static route management with metric-based priority
  - Network interface configuration (bridges, VLANs)
  - System monitoring and health checks
  - Unix socket daemon with CLI interface
